      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK CHIP (5) had some strong recent form but was below best last time when fourth (31.18) in a Grade 3/4/5 at Gawler. Generally a good beginner but was buried in the ruck off the inside last time. Has a good record here at this journey. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Worth another chance. APILLA (7) goes very well this trip starting eight times for three wins and three minors. In the money last time at this track (34.77) in a Other, finishing a one length second. Looks well placed here and among the chances. HOME TOWN (1) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing fourth (30.73) at Murray Bridge last time. Form here is sound including six wins. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Should be about the mark. SMOOTH DYNAMITE (3) collected a minor prize last start over this track and distance - must be considered.",
